The National Security and Defense Council decided to introduce a state of emergency throughout Ukraine
23 February 2022, 13:13
Photo: ©
REUTERS/Nick Iwanyshyn
Read ren.tv in
The National Security and Defense Council (NSDC) of Ukraine decided to introduce a state of emergency throughout Ukraine, with the exception of the Donetsk and Lugansk regions. The initiative must be approved by the Verkhovna Rada. This was announced by Secretary of the National Security and Defense Council Alexey Danilov.
"
The decision was made. According to our legislation, the Verkhovna Rada must approve this decision within 48 hours... A state of emergency will be introduced throughout Ukraine, except for the Donetsk and Lugansk regions."
, - said Danilov.
According to him, the state of emergency is introduced for 30 days, after which it can be extended for 60 days.
Danilov noted that a state of emergency will not be introduced in the Donetsk and Lugansk regions, because a special legal regime operates there.
“Concerning the Donetsk and Luhansk regions, there is a separate regime there, it is regulated today by our legislation, they are located in a slightly different legal zone. Therefore, a state of emergency has not been introduced there, unfortunately, it has been introduced there a long time ago, starting in 2014.”
, he said.
Aggravation of the situation in Donbass
Earlier, the Donetsk and Lugansk People's Republics announced the aggravation of the situation. The republics announced the evacuation of civilians.
On February 21, the leaders of the Donbass republics turned to Russian leader Vladimir Putin with a request to recognize the independence of the DPR and LPR. The head of state held a meeting of the Security Council, after which
signed two decrees
on the recognition of republics.
Treaties of friendship and cooperation were also signed with the independent Donetsk and Lugansk people's republics. State Duma and Federation Council
ratified
agreement data.
