In Russia
The Investigative Committee established the names of mercenaries from the Right Sector and Azov in the Donbass
23 February 2022, 17:16
Photo: ©
RF IC
Read ren.tv in
The Investigative Committee identified the names of mercenaries from the extremist organization "Right Sector" * and the nationalist battalion "Azov" * and received evidence of their involvement in crimes in the Donbass. This was reported by the official representative of the Russian Investigative Committee Svetlana Petrenko.
Share
2022-02-23T17:18:21+03:00
The Investigative Committee identified 85 persons from Ukraine involved in crimes in Donbass
The Investigative Committee identified 85 persons from Ukraine involved in crimes in Donbass
The investigation established that the Right Sector was created in 2013 by four citizens of Ukraine - Yarosh, Tarasenko, Stempitsky and Voronov. They organized an extremist organization and headed it.
“Irrefutable evidence has been obtained that members of this organization and the nationalist Azov battalion committed cruel crimes against civilians of Donbass. A number of mercenaries who joined these organizations are also known by name,”
– the message says.
One of the latest defendants was Russian Anton Korolev, whose case has been sent to court. According to the investigation, Korolev, holding nationalist views, contacted Ukrainian nationalists in 2014, after which he came to Ukraine and joined Azov. There he was trained to handle weapons, explosives, and was also given knowledge of military strategy and tactics.
“In the period from 2015 to 2019, Korolev took direct part in hostilities in the south-east of Ukraine as part of this unit against the forces of the DPR people’s militia, for which he received regular financial compensation,” the report says.
Also, Russian citizens Shirobokov and Zheleznov, Azov mercenaries who participated in hostilities, were also previously convicted in absentia. They are hiding from justice on the territory of Ukraine.
“Another convict is Litvinov, who was found guilty of committing a robbery against a Russian citizen on the territory of Ukraine,” the Investigative Committee reported.
The department noted that the Investigative Committee continues to establish the identities of those involved in crimes in the Donbass.
*organizations banned in Russia
