Nebenzya: Recognition of the LPR and DPR is a consequence of Kiev’s sabotage of obligations
23 February 2022, 19:48
Photo: ©
REUTERS/Andrew Kelly
Read ren.tv in
Russia’s recognition of the independence of the Donetsk and Lugansk people’s republics is a consequence of Kiev’s sabotage of the obligations that it assumed. This opinion was expressed during the UN General Assembly by the Permanent Representative of the Russian Federation Vasily Nebenzya.
“I would like to emphasize that the decision taken by the Russian government was the result of many years of sabotage by the Ukrainian authorities of their direct obligations under a set of measures that were approved by a Security Council resolution,”
– he emphasized.
He recalled that Ukraine accepted these obligations in February 2015. Since then, he said, the Russian side has been consistently committed to this difficult internal Ukrainian compromise.
"We did everything to preserve the sovereignty and territorial integrity of our neighboring country,"
– added Nebenzya, emphasizing that “the Russian Federation was not and is not a party to the Minsk process.”
Earlier, he said that Kiev had been hatching a plan for revenge in Donbass from the very beginning.
The conflict in eastern Ukraine has been going on since 2014. In February 2022, the situation on the contact line between Nezalezhnaya and Donbass worsened. Against this background, Russian President Vladimir Putin signed decrees on
independence
DPR and LPR. He also instructed to ensure support for peace in these republics. According to him, Moscow recognizes the DPR and LPR within the boundaries within which the heads of the republics exercise their powers. According to VTsIOM,
the majority of Russians supported the recognition of the DPR and LPR
.
